        // Handle transition
    }
}
```

We should have:

2. Analytical approach:
```cpp
// Surface would provide:
struct PathSolution {
    double edge_intersection_t;  // Exact t where path hits edge
    ParamIndex edge_param;      // Which parameter (u/v) hits bound
    ParamBound edge_bound;      // Which bound is hit
};
virtual std::optional<PathSolution> solve_path_intersection(
    const Point& start,
    const Vector& direction
) const = 0;
```

This would let surfaces provide exact solutions for when paths hit edges, rather than stepping and checking. For example, a cube face could solve this analytically since paths are straight lines in its parameter space.

